This place is always open late at night. They have cheap good food. It isn't a "gourmet" typle place, its just your classic little hole in the wall with good food. If you are in the area and on a budget, i would totally recommend it.

This place is not going to win any awards on any category, but it does have a unique selling point that makes it stand out from the crowd. This is one of the few places that accept payment by card when every other food joint in this neighbourhood only accepts cash. It's slightly ironic that they are just beside Chase though. To be honest, this was the only reason my friend and I walked in. We were hungry and didn't have any cash, a situation which I think most can identify with.  My friend ordered the quesadilla and after a short while, our server came back to report the bad news that they were out of cheese and he had to change his order to a torta. A Mexican food joint running out of cheese? Imagine that!  I had the steak burrito and it was nothing to shout about. There was a good portion of steak in the burrito but I the quality of the meat was less than ideal. Some parts were really fatty and difficult to chew, try as hard as I could. It did the job of satisfying my hunger though.  Overall, this hole in the wall is ok for a quick bite. The funny thing is that while we were there for about an hour, they had a steady stream of customers even after lunch time. They must be doing something right.
This place is open til mid during the week and open til 3 am on the weekends.  Tacos are full sized and food is made to order...  need I say more...
